<item>
            <title>[TIKA-1877] On updating the tika-mimetypes.xml to detect .fts file format, tika detector does not return anything</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-1877</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The match value for .fts file format in tika-mimetypes.xml is &quot;SIMPLE  =                    T&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
Tika detected a .fts file as application/octet-stream. On verifying the header I found the value to be &quot;SIMPLE  =                T&quot;(just 16 spaces before = and T)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I tried the following changes-&lt;br/&gt;
Change 1) Updated the existing match value. But the build failed &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Change 2) Added a new match value &amp;lt;match value=&quot;SIMPLE  =                T&quot; type=&quot;string&quot; offset=&quot;0&quot;/&amp;gt; after the existing one.&lt;br/&gt;
But now, tika returns empty value. It neither identifies the file as .fts nor as application/octet-stream.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
